    "Figure 4 plots the average BLEU, Chrf++, and BLEURT-20 score for all 12 languages against the number of instances seen during training.",
    "We see that already at level L2, our HQL models outperform all three baselines (monolingual, multilingual, Gen&Trans) on two of the metrics despite seeing fewer total training instances.",
    "The graph also shows that each new level of the hierarchy improves performance.",
    "HQL performs on par with previous work (Gold AMRs).",
    "Table 4 compares our results with previous works on Gold AMRs."
